{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1640,"text":"This is a story about capitalism."},{"time":4779,"text":"It's a system I love"},{"time":6567,"text":"because of the successes and opportunities\nit's afforded me and millions of others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11791,"text":"I started in my 20s trading commodities,\ncotton in particular, in the pits,"},{"time":18056,"text":"and if there was ever a free market\nfree-for-all, this was it,"},{"time":21682,"text":"where men wearing ties \nbut acting like gladiators"},{"time":25300,"text":"fought literally \nand physically for a profit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29437,"text":"Fortunately, I was good enough\nthat by the time I was 30,"},{"time":32360,"text":"I was able to move into the upstairs \nworld of money management,"},{"time":36020,"text":"where I spent the next three decades\nas a global macro trader."},{"time":39572,"text":"And over that time, I've seen\na lot of crazy things in the markets,"},{"time":42846,"text":"and I've traded a lot of crazy manias."},{"time":47529,"text":"And unfortunately,"},{"time":49638,"text":"I'm sad to report that right now \nwe might be in the grips"},{"time":52938,"text":"of one of the most disastrous,\ncertainly of my career,"},{"time":56894,"text":"and one consistent takeaway is\nmanias never end well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60775,"text":"Now, over the past 50 years,"},{"time":63581,"text":"we as a society have come to view\nour companies and corporations"},{"time":69432,"text":"in a very narrow, almost\nmonomaniacal fashion"},{"time":74988,"text":"with regard to how we value them,"},{"time":78255,"text":"and we have put\nso much emphasis on profits,"},{"time":81924,"text":"on short-term quarterly\nearnings and share prices,"},{"time":84710,"text":"at the exclusion of all else."},{"time":87550,"text":"It's like we've ripped the humanity\nout of our companies."},{"time":92319,"text":"Now, we don't do that --\nconveniently reduce something"},{"time":96313,"text":"to a set of numbers that you\ncan play with like Lego toys --"},{"time":99521,"text":"we don't do that in our individual life."},{"time":101869,"text":"We don't treat somebody or value them"},{"time":105072,"text":"based on their monthly income \nor their credit score,"},{"time":109213,"text":"but we have this double standard"},{"time":111020,"text":"when it comes to the way\nthat we value our businesses,"},{"time":113565,"text":"and you know what?"},{"time":115050,"text":"It's threatening the very\nunderpinnings of our society."},{"time":118215,"text":"And here's how you'll see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119817,"text":"This chart is corporate profit margins\ngoing back 40 years"},{"time":124322,"text":"as a percentage of revenues,"},{"time":126400,"text":"and you can see that we're\nat a 40-year high of 12.5 percent."},{"time":130707,"text":"Now, hooray if you're a shareholder,\n"},{"time":134259,"text":"but if you're the other side of that,\nand you're the average American worker,"},{"time":138526,"text":"then you can see it's not\nsuch a good thing."},{"time":141833,"text":"[\"U.S. Share of Income Going to Labor vs.\nCEO-to-Worker Compensation Ratio\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145410,"text":"Now, higher profit margins\ndo not increase societal wealth."},{"time":148527,"text":"What they actually do is they\nexacerbate income inequality,"},{"time":153766,"text":"and that's not a good thing."},{"time":156166,"text":"But intuitively, that makes sense, right?"},{"time":158627,"text":"Because if the top 10 percent\nof American families"},{"time":162250,"text":"own 90 percent of the stocks,"},{"time":164610,"text":"as they take a greater share\nof corporate profits,"},{"time":167571,"text":"then there's less wealth left\nfor the rest of society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171514,"text":"Again, income inequality\nis not a good thing."},{"time":174300,"text":"This next chart,\nmade by The Equality Trust,"},{"time":176761,"text":"shows 21 countries from Austria\nto Japan to New Zealand."},{"time":181614,"text":"On the horizontal axis\nis income inequality."},{"time":184818,"text":"The further to the right you go,\nthe greater the income inequality."},{"time":188116,"text":"On the vertical axis\nare nine social and health metrics."},{"time":191459,"text":"The more you go up that,\nthe worse the problems are,"},{"time":194222,"text":"and those metrics include life expectancy,\nteenage pregnancy, literacy,"},{"time":199470,"text":"social mobility, just to name a few."},{"time":202210,"text":"Now, those of you in the audience\nwho are Americans may wonder,"},{"time":205391,"text":"well, where does the United States rank?"},{"time":207736,"text":"Where does it lie on that chart?"},{"time":209593,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":211288,"text":"We're literally off the chart."},{"time":213970,"text":"Yes, that's us,"},{"time":215793,"text":"with the greatest income inequality"},{"time":217952,"text":"and the greatest social problems,\naccording to those metrics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222248,"text":"Now, here's a macro forecast\nthat's easy to make,"},{"time":224802,"text":"and that's, that gap between\nthe wealthiest and the poorest,"},{"time":228401,"text":"it will get closed."},{"time":230421,"text":"History always does it."},{"time":232010,"text":"It typically happens in one of three ways:"},{"time":234159,"text":"either through revolution,\nhigher taxes, or wars."},{"time":240560,"text":"None of those are on my bucket list."},{"time":242889,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244025,"text":"Now, there's another way to do it,"},{"time":246086,"text":"and that's by increasing justness\nin corporate behavior,"},{"time":250226,"text":"but the way that we're\noperating right now,"},{"time":252989,"text":"that would require\na tremendous change in behavior,"},{"time":256983,"text":"and like an addict trying to kick a habit,"},{"time":260930,"text":"the first step is to acknowledge\nthat you have a problem."},{"time":264436,"text":"And let me just say,\nthis profits mania that we're on"},{"time":268337,"text":"is so deeply entrenched"},{"time":270636,"text":"that we don't even realize\nhow we're harming society."},{"time":273167,"text":"Here's a small but startling example\nof exactly how we're doing that:"},{"time":277184,"text":"this chart shows corporate giving"},{"time":280247,"text":"as a percentage of profits, \nnot revenues, over the last 30 years."},{"time":285632,"text":"Juxtapose that to the earlier chart\nof corporate profit margins,"},{"time":291401,"text":"and I ask you, does that feel right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296758,"text":"In all fairness, when I\nstarted writing this, I thought,"},{"time":299699,"text":"\"Oh wow, what does my company,\nwhat does Tudor do?\""},{"time":302160,"text":"And I realized we give one percent\nof corporate profits"},{"time":307693,"text":"to charity every year."},{"time":309423,"text":"And I'm supposed to be a philanthropist."},{"time":313324,"text":"When I realized that, I literally\nwanted to throw up."},{"time":319623,"text":"But the point is, this mania\nis so deeply entrenched"},{"time":322101,"text":"that well-intentioned people like myself\ndon't even realize that we're part of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327943,"text":"Now, we're not going\nto change corporate behavior"},{"time":330274,"text":"by simply increasing corporate\nphilanthropy or charitable contributions."},{"time":335591,"text":"And oh, by the way,\nwe've since quadrupled that,"},{"time":338725,"text":"but -- (Applause) -- Please."},{"time":342974,"text":"But we can do it by driving\nmore just behavior."},{"time":346713,"text":"And one way to do it is actually trusting"},{"time":349754,"text":"the system that got us\nhere in the first place,"},{"time":352169,"text":"and that's the free market system."},{"time":354282,"text":"About a year ago,\nsome friends of mine and I"},{"time":356975,"text":"started a not-for-profit\ncalled Just Capital."},{"time":360025,"text":"Its mission is very simple:"},{"time":361493,"text":"to help companies and corporations"},{"time":363988,"text":"learn how to operate in a more just\nfashion by using the public's input"},{"time":369263,"text":"to define exactly what the criteria are\nfor just corporate behavior."},{"time":375574,"text":"Now, right now, there's\nno widely accepted standard"},{"time":377989,"text":"that a company or corporation can follow,\nand that's where Just Capital comes in,"},{"time":382331,"text":"because beginning this year and every year\nwe'll be conducting a nationwide survey"},{"time":387651,"text":"of a representative sample\nof 20,000 Americans"},{"time":391781,"text":"to find out exactly what they think"},{"time":394701,"text":"are the criteria for justness\nin corporate behavior."},{"time":398579,"text":"Now, this is a model that's going\nto start in the United States"},{"time":401591,"text":"but can be expanded\nanywhere around the globe,"},{"time":404226,"text":"and maybe we'll find out"},{"time":406107,"text":"that the most important\nthing for the public"},{"time":408975,"text":"is that we create living wage jobs,\nor make healthy products,"},{"time":414326,"text":"or help, not harm, the environment."},{"time":417577,"text":"At Just Capital, we don't know,\nand it's not for us to decide."},{"time":421850,"text":"We're but messengers,"},{"time":423846,"text":"but we have 100 percent confidence \nand faith in the American public"},{"time":427956,"text":"to get it right."},{"time":429880,"text":"So we'll release the findings\nthis September for the first time,"},{"time":433410,"text":"and then next year, we'll poll again,"},{"time":435850,"text":"and we'll take the additive step this time"},{"time":438149,"text":"of ranking the 1,000\nlargest U.S. companies"},{"time":441168,"text":"from number one to number 1,000\nand everything in between."},{"time":445720,"text":"We're calling it the Just Index,"},{"time":448551,"text":"and remember, we're an independent\nnot-for-profit with no bias,"},{"time":453800,"text":"and we will be giving\nthe American public a voice."},{"time":458953,"text":"And maybe over time, we'll find out\nthat as people come to know"},{"time":463156,"text":"which companies are the most just,"},{"time":465176,"text":"human and economic resources\nwill be driven towards them,"},{"time":469216,"text":"and they'll become the most prosperous"},{"time":471190,"text":"and help our country\nbe the most prosperous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475351,"text":"Now, capitalism has been responsible\nfor every major innovation"},{"time":479457,"text":"that's made this world a more inspiring\nand wonderful place to live in."},{"time":484578,"text":"Capitalism has to be based on justice."},{"time":487443,"text":"It has to be, and now more than ever,"},{"time":489649,"text":"with economic divisions\ngrowing wider every day."},{"time":493480,"text":"It's estimated that 47 percent\nof American workers"},{"time":496498,"text":"can be displaced in the next 20 years."},{"time":499796,"text":"I'm not against progress."},{"time":501769,"text":"I want the driverless car and the jet pack\njust like everyone else."},{"time":506650,"text":"But I'm pleading for recognition\nthat with increased wealth and profits"},{"time":512500,"text":"has to come greater\ncorporate social responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517930,"text":"\"If justice is removed,\" said Adam Smith,\nthe father of capitalism,"},{"time":523665,"text":"\"the great, the immense fabric\nof human society must in a moment"},{"time":529419,"text":"crumble into atoms.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":533626,"text":"Now, when I was young,\nand there was a problem,"},{"time":537390,"text":"my mama used to always\nsigh and shake her head and say,"},{"time":541573,"text":"\"Have mercy, have mercy.\""},{"time":545630,"text":"Now's not the time for us,\nfor the rest of us to show them mercy."},{"time":550181,"text":"The time is now for us\nto show them fairness,"},{"time":553370,"text":"and we can do that, you and I,"},{"time":555846,"text":"by starting where we work,\nin the businesses that we operate in."},{"time":561100,"text":"And when we put justness\non par with profits,"},{"time":564460,"text":"we'll get the most wonderful thing\nin all the world."},{"time":568408,"text":"We'll take back our humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571774,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574421,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}